{# gap-register-row.tera: Renders a gap register entry. #}
{# Constitutional Equation: gap section = mu(wasm4pm-compat.ttl, GapRegisterEntry) #}
{# Input variables: #}
{#   gapId        — unique gap identifier, e.g. "GAP-007" #}
{#   severity     — one of: BLOCKER | HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW #}
{#   title        — short title for the gap #}
{#   description  — full description of what is missing or wrong #}
{#   resolution   — what must happen to close this gap #}
{#   blockedBy    — comma-separated list of issues/gaps this is blocked by; empty if none #}
{#   enables      — comma-separated list of capabilities/papers this gap's closure enables #}
{# Output: markdown section for the gap register #}
{# Auto-generated by ggen from wasm4pm-compat.ttl --- DO NOT EDIT #}

### {{ gapId }}: {{ title }}

**Severity:** {{ severity }}

{{ description }}

**Resolution:** {{ resolution }}

{% if blockedBy %}
**Blocked by:** {% for blocker in blockedBy %}{{ blocker }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
{% if enables | length > 0 %}
**Enables:** {% for cap in enables %}{{ cap }}{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}

{% endif %}
